name: Quintiles
definition: A quintile is one of five equal groups that a population can be divided into according to the distribution of values of a particular variable.

values.name: First Quintile
values.definition: Quantile < 0.20. The lowest 20% of the range of possible values.

values.name: Second Quintile
values.definition: 0.20 <= Quantile < 0.40. The second lowest 20% of the range of possible values.

values.name: Third Quintile
values.definition: 0.40 <= Quantile < 0.60. The middle 20% of the range of possible values.

values.name: Fourth Quintile
values.definition: 0.60 <= Quantile < 0.80. The second highest 20% of the range of possible values.

values.name: Fifth Quintile
values.definition: 0.80 <= Quantile <= 1.0. The highest 20% of the range of possible values.
